{
  "text": "Beta diversity will provide other perspectives on species rarity (Gaston 1994; [CITATION_1] . The point for consideration is whether spatio-temporal variation in community composition affords opportunities for rare species to persist. The proportion of rare species in a community may be influenced by the dispersal ability and habitat requirements of individual species, which generate beta diversity [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Developing hypotheses on the relationship between species rarity and beta diversity will shed more light on species diversity and community assembly in the future.",
